Introduction¶

This project explore the Prosper loan loan data set. The data set contains 113,937 observations 81 variables which includes, loan amount, borrower rate (or interest rate), current loan status, borrower income, and many others.

What is prosper loan ?¶

For a better understanding of the data set we are working with, lets briefly explain what the prosper loan platform is about.

Prosper loan is an online loaning network involving peer-to-peer lending using the platform prosper.com. This platform allows borrowers to make post listings of loans requests. Interested lenders make their bids on these listings which becomes a loan when the lender invest his/her money by funding the full amount requested by borrower. Some of the informations contains are the time at which the loan originated, the amount requested, the loan status, the credit grade or rating of the borrower, the lender rate and the borrower rate. see http://konect.cc/networks/prosper-loans/ .

What is the structure of your dataset?¶

The data set contains 81 features or columns and 113936 of observations or rows. The data types of the features present are bool(3), float64(50), int64(11), object(17). Some of the features contains significant missing values which are due to one of the followings:

  1. The borrower not having prior loans when the listing was made. For example we have features like TotalProsperLoans, TotalProsperPaymentsBilled, OnTimeProsperPayments,ProsperPaymentsLessThanOneMonthLate, ProsperPaymentsOneMonthPlusLate,ProsperPrincipalBorrowed,ProsperPrincipalOutstanding,ScorexChangeAtTimeOfListing.

  2. Features that are only applicable after July 2009. For example, EstimatedEffectiveYield, EstimatedLoss, EstimatedReturn, ProsperRating (numeric), ProsperRating (Alpha), ProsperScore.

What is/are the main feature(s) of interest in your dataset?¶

First of all, major feature of interest to me in the data set is the BorrowerAPI. That is what feature(s) affect the borrower's annual percentage rate?

It will also be interesting to understand the Loanstatus. That is what affects the outcome of the loan?

What features in the dataset do you think will help support your investigation into your feature(s) of interest?¶

The features in the dataset I think will support my chosen features of interest are IncomeRange, BorrowerAPR, DebtToIncomeRatio, ProsperScore, CreditScoreRangeLower and CreditScoreRangeUpper.

def barchartplot(data, catvar):
    '''Takes in a dataset and a cathigorical variable in the dataset 
    as an input and plots a barchart as an output'''
    colors=sb.color_palette()[0]
    plt.figure(figsize=(10,8))

Next we investigate the distribution of the borrower's Annual percentage range.

In the prosper loan system, the Annual percentage range of a prosper borrower refer to the closing fee charged when you make your first borrow request. This fee is taken out of the loan amount you requested when the loan originates. Hence, the amount financed is always less than the borrower request amounts although the borrower pays back the full amount he requested.

For example: A Prosper borrower with a B rating receives 2,425 in cash for a requested 2,500 loan. The difference of 75 is the closing fee that Prosper collects on the loan. However, the borrower is still responsible for paying back the full 2,500 over the term of the loan.

The credit score helps to determines your creditworthiness, or how much of a risk it is for a lender to loan money to you. The higher the score the better it is for u to get a loan. According to prosper.com, Equifax ranking is as shown below:

Below 580: Poor credit

580669: Fair credit

670739: Good credit

740799: Very good credit

800 and above: Excellent credit

According to prosper.com, consumers in the 670 and up range generally have no trouble qualifying for credit commensurate with their income. People between 580669 can still qualify for lines of credit, but will likely have to pay higher interest rates if they qualify for credit. However, those with scores below 580 may struggle to qualify for financing at all .

Conclusions¶

The project goal was to investigate the features that affects the Borrower's annual percentage rate according to the data set. Additionally, the project also investigates the outcome of the loan and factors that are likely to affect the loan outcome. The supporting features selected are: IncomeRange, Loanstatus, DebtToIncomeRatio, ProsperScore, CreditScoreRangeLower and CreditScoreRangeUpper

We observed that the prosper score has a great influence on the the borrowerAPR and even the outcome of the loan. The prosper score determine the risk of a customer defaulting in his loan. High prosper score means low risk and vice-versa.

Borrowers who are seen to be of lower risk of defaulting in their loan are giving a lower annual percentage range. They have also show according to the dataset to have low probability of defaulting.

We also observed that having a high prosper score and credit score will drastically reduce the borrower's APR.
